'''''X-Wing: Wraith Squadron''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] novel written by [[Aaron Allston]]. It is the fifth volume of the [[Star Wars: X-Wing (novel series)|''Star Wars: X-Wing'' novel series]], and it was first published by [[Bantam Spectra]] on [[February 2]], [[1998]]. A sequel, ''[[X-Wing: Iron Fist]]'', was published later that year.

==Publisher's summary==
''They are the galaxy's most elite fighting force. And as the battle against the Empire rages, the X-wing pilots risk life and machine to protect the Rebel Alliance. Now they must go on a daring undercover mission&mdash;as the crew of an Imperial warship.''

''It is Wedge Antilles' boldest creation: a covert-action unit of X-wing fighters, its pilots drawn from the dregs of other units, castoffs and rejects given one last chance. But before the new pilots can complete their training, the squadron's base is attacked by former Imperial Admiral Trigit, and Wraith Squadron is forced to swing into action&mdash;taking over an Imperial warship and impersonating its crew. The mission: to gain vital intelligence about Trigit's secret weapons, to sabotage the admiral's plans, and to lure him into an Alliance trap. But the high-stakes gamble pits Wraith Squadron's ragtag renegades against the Empire's most brilliant master of guile and deception.''

''Are they up to the challenge?''

''If not, the penalty is instant death.''

==Plot summary==
[[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] creates a bold new experimental [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]] comprising cross-trained [[Commando/Legends|commando]]/[[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] who were once washouts and castaways from other units. Wedge believes he can shape such misfits into an effective special missions team for the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic's]] campaign to stop the destruction waged by [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Warlord/Legends|warlord]] [[Zsinj|Zsinj]]. Among the new pilots are [[Sniper/Legends|sniper]] [[Myn Donos]], sole survivor of [[Talon Squadron (New Republic)|Talon Squadron]]; [[Voort saBinring|Voort "Piggy" saBinring]], a biologically modified [[Gamorrean/Legends|Gamorrean]] whose unnatural skills are a result of [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] experimentation; and [[Kell Tainer]], a demolitions expert whose [[Parent/Legends|father]], [[Kissek Doran]], was [[Death/Legends|killed]] by fellow pilot [[Wes Janson/Legends|Wes Janson]] after Doran's panic attacks jeopardized a crucial [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] mission.

The new [[Wraith Squadron|Wraith Squadron's]] training [[Folor Base|base on Folor]] comes under attack from Imperial [[Admiral/Legends|admiral]] [[Apwar Trigit|Trigit]] and his [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyer]] [[Implacable (Star Destroyer)/Legends|''Implacable'']]. The Wraiths use unorthodox tactics to delay and distract Trigit, allowing for the base's successful evacuation. Regrouping at [[Xobome 6]], the Wraiths commandeer one of Zsinj's [[CR90 corvette/Legends|corvettes]], the [[Ession Strike|''Night Caller'']]. Posing as the ''Night Caller's'' crew, the squadron uses the ship in secret missions against the warlord's scattered outposts and business ventures. Facilitating this deception are the acting skills of Wraith pilot [[Garik Loran|Garik "Face" Loran]], who poses at the corvette's [[Captain/Legends|captain]].

Despite their actions against Zsinj, the warlord does not suspect the true nature of the ''Night Caller's'' crew – he mistakenly believes the corvette to be shadowed by New Republic [[Agent/Legends|agents]]. Zsinj informs the ''Night Caller'' of his plan to attack New Republic forces on [[Ession]]. With the New Republic prepared for the assault, they defeat Admiral Trigit's Star Destroyer. Myn Donos exacts justice on Trigit for the destruction of Talon Squadron by shooting him down in his attempt escape. [[Gara Petothel]], Trigit's mistress and an [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Imperial Intelligence]] agent secretly loyal to Zsinj, escapes the fallout in a [[Escape pod/Legends|escape pod]] after carefully crafting an alias for herself for the purposes of infiltrating the New Republic. Though their victories prove costly, the Wraith Squadron experiment is nonetheless successful, and Wedge is determined to continue his hunt for Warlord Zsinj. 

